HEADWORD: Gringo
<hw>Grin"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Amer. Sp., fr. Sp.
<ets>gringo</ets> gibberish; cf. <ets>griego</ets> Greek, F.
<ets>grigou</ets> wretch.]</ety> <def>Among Spanish Americans, a
foreigner, especially an American or sometimes an Englishman; -- often
used disparagingly or as a term of reproach.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

